The paper deals with the problem of clustering in arbitrary metrics and Euclidean space, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper proposes a novel algorithm based on the greedy method for solving the problem of $k$-center clustering with outliers. This problem is closely related to the field of data structures (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data mining (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the construction of coresets, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DM, and cs.CG.
